    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="169"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.24/440: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-29">March 29,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>399. Your 516 of March 22.<note n="10" xml:id="d169fn10">Not printed.</note> The
                    Board of Economic Warfare is now certifying, and will continue during the 60-day
                    period to certify for shipment, only those materials listed in despatch no.
                        1582<note n="11" xml:id="d169fn11">Not printed; this list was a selection of
                        articles according to Schedule B. Schedule B was a statistical
                        classification of domestic and foreign commodities exported from the United
                        States, drawn up by the Bureau of the Census, Department of Commerce.</note>
                    as importable. The Embassy should, however, bear in mind that materials <pb
                        facs="0187" n="175" xml:id="pg_175"/> covered by general license and
                    weighing less than 2240 pounds do not require certification by the Board of
                    Economic Warfare and some such shipments, even though considered non-essential,
                    will undoubtedly continue to arrive until the Decentralization Plan is fully
                    effective.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
